[src:aspnet-core/asp-net-core] Originally deemed **ASP.NET vNext**, the framework was going to be called **ASP.NET 5** when ready.
[src:aspnet-core/asp-net-core] However, in order to avoid implying it is an update to the existing ASP.NET framework, Microsoft later changed the name to ASP.NET Core at the 1.0 release.
[src:aspnet-core/asp-net-mvc] ASP.NET Core has since been released, which unified ASP.NET, ASP.NET MVC, ASP.NET Web API, and ASP.NET Web Pages (a platform using only Razor pages).
[src:aspnet-core/asp-net-mvc] MVC 6 was abandoned due to Core and is not expected to be released.
